WEBVTT

00:00.959 --> 00:03.962
♪♪

00:38.997 --> 00:43.460
-Thanks, Andy.
-Did you drink?

00:43.460 --> 00:46.254
-Don't yell at me, all right?
-No.

00:48.465 --> 00:52.302
I feel like,
if I could drink,
then I could be with Bobby.

00:52.302 --> 00:56.473
-So then you know
what that means.
-But I want to be with him.

00:58.433 --> 01:02.437
I'm gonna lose him.
Maybe I already did.

01:04.230 --> 01:08.359
Whatever else is going on,
you can't add booze.

01:08.359 --> 01:10.278
So just never
be happy, right?

01:10.278 --> 01:13.448
When I drank,
I could work good--

01:13.448 --> 01:15.658
not feel like such a whore.

01:15.658 --> 01:18.453
-Don't talk like that.
-You feel
how you feel, Andy.

01:18.453 --> 01:20.830
Sending me back undercover,
shaking it up for Liery--

01:20.830 --> 01:23.458
It's like the--
The job knew what I was.

01:23.458 --> 01:26.377
Bobby, the squad--
I was kidding myself
with all that.

01:26.377 --> 01:29.422
You know what
you're saying's not right.

01:29.422 --> 01:31.007
I want a drink.

01:31.800 --> 01:34.469
Add hiding
to everything else.

01:34.469 --> 01:36.805
Hiding's got a lot
of pluses.

01:36.805 --> 01:38.681
(pager beeping)

01:42.393 --> 01:44.479
(pager beeping)

01:46.648 --> 01:48.691
-The squad.
-Me too.

01:50.693 --> 01:53.822
You wanna stop home
and change?

01:53.822 --> 01:55.323
Yeah.

02:01.663 --> 02:03.581
(sniffles)

02:05.500 --> 02:08.086
Something's going on
inside of you.

02:08.086 --> 02:13.049
Something's brewing up.
You gotta hold on.

02:15.093 --> 02:17.971
Thanks for coming, Andy.

02:17.971 --> 02:19.180
Don't drink.

02:20.849 --> 02:21.891
No.

02:35.864 --> 02:38.867
♪♪

03:43.097 --> 03:46.100
♪♪

04:08.206 --> 04:10.416
We're over here.

04:10.416 --> 04:12.627
Hey. What do we got?

04:12.627 --> 04:15.421
Mike Zorzi--
got in the middle
of a stickup.

04:15.421 --> 04:18.466
Put down one of the perps.
The other one fled
on foot.

04:18.466 --> 04:20.677
He gave me a description.
I put it out.

04:20.677 --> 04:23.471
-Zorzi's off-duty?
-He's workin' days.

04:23.471 --> 04:25.682
-You got an I.D.
on this D.O.A. perp?
-Nope.

04:25.682 --> 04:29.102
How about this other guy?
That's Tony Moore--
The singer.

04:29.102 --> 04:31.437
Zorzi was giving him a ride
from the airport.

04:31.437 --> 04:34.440
-Tony Moore?
-Yeah. Had a hell
of a sweet voice.

04:34.440 --> 04:37.277
-Okay, thanks, Shannon.
-Okay.

04:38.528 --> 04:41.447
Want me to start
a canvass?

04:41.447 --> 04:42.282
How's it going?

04:42.282 --> 04:45.076
Okay. What do you
want me to do?

04:46.661 --> 04:49.664
Take down
the license plate numbers
of the cars in the area here.

04:49.664 --> 04:52.917
They could have
parked along here
before ripping this guy off.

04:58.923 --> 05:02.802
-Tony Moore, huh?
-Let's go talk to Zorzi.

05:02.802 --> 05:04.762
Mm-hmm.

05:10.310 --> 05:13.271
So you guys drive in
from the squad?

05:13.271 --> 05:15.315
We were having
a cup of coffee.

05:15.315 --> 05:16.899
(radio chatter)

05:16.899 --> 05:20.987
-Zorzi, how you feel?
-I knew him my whole life, man.

05:21.863 --> 05:24.490
-Hey, Detective.
-Hey. We're glad
you're okay.

05:24.490 --> 05:27.493
So how'd this go down?

05:27.493 --> 05:30.288
(clears throat)
I stopped here
to get cigarettes.

05:30.288 --> 05:33.624
I'm coming out,
two Spanish guys
got Tony out of the car.

05:33.624 --> 05:36.169
-That one's got a gun on him.
-All right, back up.

05:36.169 --> 05:40.173
-You picked Tony up
from the airport?
-He had flew in from Vegas.

05:40.173 --> 05:41.966
I'm half a bodyguard.
He would get paranoid.

05:41.966 --> 05:44.344
You know, those $10,000 rings
he's got on.

05:44.344 --> 05:48.097
-So you come out of the store.
-I draw my weapon.

05:48.097 --> 05:50.975
Tony's saying,
"Mike, shoot the sons
of bitches."

05:50.975 --> 05:53.353
Scared out of his wits.

05:53.353 --> 05:55.521
Before I know what,

05:55.521 --> 05:59.150
the scumbag puts a couple
of rounds into him
point blank.

05:59.150 --> 06:01.736
I pull off two shots
and manage to take
the one guy down.

06:01.736 --> 06:02.945
What happened to the second guy?

06:02.945 --> 06:05.531
The second guy grabbed
the attaché case
that Tony's got.

06:05.531 --> 06:07.158
-He takes off running.
-You fired at him?

06:07.158 --> 06:10.328
Just wanted to see
how Tony was doing.
Then I went and called it in.

06:10.328 --> 06:14.332
-What did he have
in the attaché case?
-Thieving scumbag.

06:14.332 --> 06:15.958
I don't even know what
he thought he was getting.

06:15.958 --> 06:19.212
The only thing Tony
kept in there was,
like, sheet music.

06:19.212 --> 06:21.798
But you got a good solid look
at the second guy?

06:21.798 --> 06:25.218
Oh, yeah. Yeah.
Gave Shannon a description.

06:25.218 --> 06:27.720
All right, go to the house.
We'll get a statement.

06:29.389 --> 06:31.808
Do you remember
"By Candlelight," Detective?

06:31.808 --> 06:34.227
Tony and the Tremonts,
summer of '64?

06:34.227 --> 06:36.562
There was a lot
of doo-wop records out.

06:36.562 --> 06:38.981
If I could carry a tune
I would sing it for you.

06:38.981 --> 06:40.400
You would know.

06:49.409 --> 06:52.412
♪♪

06:57.083 --> 06:59.377
Yeah. Yeah, all right.

07:00.586 --> 07:02.797
Copy I.A.B. on all your fives.

07:02.797 --> 07:05.842
Okay. So the D.O.A. perp
is a Joseph Vasquez.

07:05.842 --> 07:10.263
He's got two robbery collars
with the same partner--
Roberto Roca.

07:10.263 --> 07:12.432
This Roca doesn't
fit the description
that Zorzi gave us,

07:12.432 --> 07:15.435
-but, you know, we'll see
what he has to say.
-Anything off canvass?

07:15.435 --> 07:18.563
Four different people
heard shots.
Nobody saw anything.

07:20.314 --> 07:24.235
M.E. says the D.O.A. victim
had cocaine residue
in his nostrils.

07:24.235 --> 07:26.237
Tony Moore?

07:26.237 --> 07:29.240
Did Mike Zorzi mention anything
while you were talking to him
during the night...

07:29.240 --> 07:31.617
-about Moore using coke?
-Uh-uh.

07:31.617 --> 07:34.245
He did find time to talk
about how tight they were.

07:34.245 --> 07:37.081
Maybe he's protecting
his buddy's reputation.

07:37.081 --> 07:39.417
One possibility.

07:39.417 --> 07:41.252
Zorzi's gonna have to get
dole-tested.

07:41.252 --> 07:44.338
(sighs)
Yeah.

07:44.338 --> 07:46.674
-You want me to tell him?
-No.

07:46.674 --> 07:50.094
Let's give him a chance
to tell us what
he left out.

07:50.094 --> 07:52.472
Either of you
know Zorzi personally?

07:52.472 --> 07:54.474
He wasn't a drinker,
about all I can say.

07:54.474 --> 07:56.976
-I never saw him
in the bars.
-I barely know the guy.

07:56.976 --> 07:57.894
Yeah.

07:59.270 --> 08:01.856
Grew up on the same street
in the Bronx,

08:01.856 --> 08:05.610
back when it was--
(chuckles)
Mauriello--

08:05.610 --> 08:07.278
Before he changed it.

08:07.278 --> 08:10.072
-Tony Mauriello, huh?
-I can remember
those guys...

08:10.072 --> 08:12.658
hanging on the corner,
harmonizing--
Man.

08:12.658 --> 08:16.662
Young kid. I couldn't think
of nothing cooler than that.

08:16.662 --> 08:18.539
Excuse me, Zorzi.
We need a minute.

08:18.539 --> 08:23.085
-Yeah, sure, sure.
-Hey, you guys are gonna
catch that other bum, right?

08:23.085 --> 08:26.506
-That's our plan.
-Tony was a great guy.
He loved cops.

08:26.506 --> 08:29.509
You know, he showed up
and sang at Rich Libey's
retirement racket.

08:29.509 --> 08:32.720
Hmm. Did you get some rest?

08:32.720 --> 08:35.515
Yeah, some.
Listen, I was gonna
come talk to you.

08:35.515 --> 08:37.725
Tony being who he was,
you know,

08:37.725 --> 08:40.353
there's probably
gonna be reporters, TV.

08:40.353 --> 08:41.896
I want my name
left out of it.

08:41.896 --> 08:44.106
We weren't planning
on talking to any press.

08:44.106 --> 08:47.485
This other scumbag being
at large, I don't want to
put my family in jeopardy.

08:47.485 --> 08:51.489
Let me ask you.
Tony Moore have a cocaine habit
you were aware of?

08:51.489 --> 08:52.907
You saying there was coke
in his system?

08:52.907 --> 08:56.327
You know, those stickup guys--
Maybe they figured that's what
was in Tony's briefcase.

08:56.327 --> 08:59.205
If I knew that,
I wouldn't hide it
from you fellas.

08:59.872 --> 09:02.583
Well, listen--
This is out of our hands,

09:02.583 --> 09:05.711
but we're gonna need you
to get dole-tested.

09:05.711 --> 09:08.381
(laughs)
Say what?

09:08.381 --> 09:10.174
Hey, you know the way
this job is.

09:10.174 --> 09:12.176
Anything involved
with drugs, you know.

09:12.176 --> 09:15.179
-You don't mind, do you?
-Do I mind?

09:15.179 --> 09:17.974
Listen, if Tony
had went into the john
at La Guardia...

09:17.974 --> 09:19.976
and did something,
I don't know.

09:19.976 --> 09:22.186
But what I could swear to is,
I never saw him use.

09:22.186 --> 09:25.147
I never saw him
in possession.
He respected cops.

09:25.147 --> 09:28.150
And he respected me.
He would never put me
in that kind of spot.

09:28.150 --> 09:31.195
Well, you still need to go
to Health Services.

09:32.321 --> 09:34.740
Miller, you hear this over here?
They figure me for a coke hound.

09:34.740 --> 09:38.619
-Whoa, whoa. Hold on, Zorzi.
-No, no, man. You got it.

09:41.414 --> 09:44.166
Hey, Sarge.
I gotta go over
to LeFrak City,

09:44.166 --> 09:47.545
piss in a cup
to satisfy these detectives.

09:47.545 --> 09:50.423
-Go pick up Bobby Rock, huh?
-Hey, Bobby. Hey, Andy.

09:50.423 --> 09:54.010
-What do you got?
-D.O.A. dump job
over on Avenue "B."

09:54.010 --> 09:56.220
They brought you guys in early
off that shooting
last night, huh?

09:56.220 --> 10:01.225
-SIPOWICZ: Yeah.
-Hey! You're sending Mike Zorzi
to get dole-tested?

10:01.225 --> 10:03.227
He risked his life
trying to save his buddy.

10:03.227 --> 10:06.397
-Sarge, you know we can't
talk about the case.
-Who's the good guy here?

10:06.397 --> 10:08.190
Nobody's making him a bad guy.

10:08.190 --> 10:11.569
Well, then why's
he have to get doled?
He's 15 years on the job.

10:11.569 --> 10:14.780
You mind just letting us
run our investigation
here, Sarge?

10:14.780 --> 10:16.198
Thank you.

10:20.786 --> 10:23.998
Next time we want to talk
to Zorzi we take him
up to the squad.

10:33.716 --> 10:35.217
(sighs)

10:39.138 --> 10:42.224
Russell's upset.
She's looking not to drink.

10:43.267 --> 10:45.061
She tell you
to tell me this?

10:45.061 --> 10:46.604
-No. I'm telling you
on my own.
-So, what--

10:46.604 --> 10:51.859
You're not breaking any kind
of 12-step secret handshake
here, giving her up?

10:51.859 --> 10:53.319
Sorry.

10:56.030 --> 10:59.241
You know, she comes
over to my place after
this asshole Liery got it,

10:59.241 --> 11:02.620
and she seems like she's
getting past whatever it was
that was hanging her up.

11:02.620 --> 11:05.456
-What did she say that was?
-Something about being
unsure of herself.

11:05.456 --> 11:08.042
She talked about...

11:08.042 --> 11:10.461
flirting with boys
in high school,

11:10.461 --> 11:14.674
-showing off her figure.
-Said she feels like a whore.

11:14.674 --> 11:16.467
She told you that?

11:16.467 --> 11:18.511
Well, what the hell
is she talking about?

11:18.511 --> 11:20.096
She talking about
this Liery drugging her?

11:20.096 --> 11:22.682
-Is that what she's
talking about?
-I don't think so.

11:22.682 --> 11:26.102
All's I know,
she's gotta hold on.
Not drink on top of it.

11:26.102 --> 11:30.272
Well, Andy, I can't
hold her hand no more, man.

11:30.272 --> 11:33.401
And I can't stop her
from bringing the drink
to her mouth.

11:40.032 --> 11:42.910
We should pick up
this Bobby Rock.

11:44.495 --> 11:47.498
♪♪

11:51.085 --> 11:53.087
KIRKENDALL:
Overkill-type stabbing wounds.

11:53.087 --> 11:55.715
The girl can't
be older than 17.

11:55.715 --> 11:59.927
Is that an earring
in her navel?
One of those pierce jobs?

11:59.927 --> 12:02.138
Yeah. Plus a couple
of tattoos.

12:02.138 --> 12:04.724
If I'd set foot
in my parents' house
with any of this crap--

12:04.724 --> 12:06.726
Yeah, I know.

12:06.726 --> 12:09.562
If I let slip a curse word
anywheres close to my old man--

12:09.562 --> 12:12.690
-Pow. Right across the mouth.
-Yeah, but it
taught you respect.

12:12.690 --> 12:15.151
Yeah, no earrings in my navel.

12:16.152 --> 12:18.529
-Did you find any I.D.?
-Nah.

12:18.529 --> 12:22.533
Whoa! Check this out.

12:22.533 --> 12:25.703
"Crush-O-Rama number 18,
starring Michelle."

12:27.872 --> 12:30.332
Yeah, that's her.

12:33.335 --> 12:35.713
What's "Crush-O-Rama"
supposed to mean?

12:35.713 --> 12:39.383
I get the feeling
it's not from the "G" section
at Blockbuster.

12:44.764 --> 12:46.599
Bobby Rock, Bobby Rock.

12:46.599 --> 12:50.186
Have a seat right there.

12:50.186 --> 12:52.730
What were you doing
last night?

12:53.564 --> 12:55.566
I wasn't doing anything.

12:55.566 --> 12:58.736
-No? You weren't hanging out
with your boy Joe Vasquez?
-Not last night.

12:58.736 --> 13:00.946
You and Joe get tired
of robbing gas stations?

13:00.946 --> 13:04.158
You figure you'll take off
this good-looking Italian
for his jewelry?

13:04.158 --> 13:08.162
-Not me.
-So then what were you doing
last night?

13:09.955 --> 13:12.374
I was watching
the Knicks game on TV.

13:12.374 --> 13:15.127
Watching the Knicks, huh?
Anybody with you?

13:15.127 --> 13:17.755
-By myself.
-That's a bad break then,
for you.

13:17.755 --> 13:21.217
Look, I wasn't with Joe
last night, okay?

13:21.217 --> 13:22.384
But I tell you this--

13:23.427 --> 13:26.806
I wish I knew who it was...

13:26.806 --> 13:29.016
-who shot and killed him.
-Oh, yeah? Why is that?

13:29.016 --> 13:32.228
-I just would like to know.
-You and Joe Vasquez are tight.

13:32.228 --> 13:36.190
You're sorry to see him dead.
I can understand that.
You know what I can't figure?

13:36.190 --> 13:39.276
You all being so tight,
him doing this stickup
without you.

13:39.276 --> 13:42.530
-Look, if I was with him,
watching his back--
-Mm-hmm?

13:42.530 --> 13:43.781
I tell you this--

13:43.781 --> 13:45.783
It would be
a whole different story.

13:45.783 --> 13:49.203
Yeah? Well, maybe you got
some idea who it was...

13:49.203 --> 13:50.996
supposed to be
watching his back
if it wasn't you.

13:50.996 --> 13:54.208
How about that, Roberto, huh?
Who it could have been
cut and ran...

13:54.208 --> 13:56.210
while your buddy was
breathing his last breath.

13:56.210 --> 13:59.421
(groans, chuckles)
I wish I knew that too,

13:59.421 --> 14:04.468
because I'd be taking care
of it all by myself
without troubling you all.

14:04.468 --> 14:07.596
That's not how
you should be looking
at this, Roberto.

14:07.596 --> 14:09.598
The way you should be
looking at it,

14:09.598 --> 14:14.061
you count yourself lucky you
didn't catch a couple of hot
ones in the chest yourself.

14:14.061 --> 14:17.022
Do you hear what
I'm saying to you? Huh?

14:17.022 --> 14:19.024
You count yourself lucky.

14:19.024 --> 14:22.903
You don't go worrying
about who shot who.

14:22.903 --> 14:24.238
Are we done?

14:24.238 --> 14:26.824
You stand in a lineup?

14:26.824 --> 14:30.286
If this asshole will
let go of my jaw.

14:34.957 --> 14:35.875
Yeah.

14:36.876 --> 14:38.460
I'll stand in your lineup.

14:44.508 --> 14:47.511
♪♪

14:51.181 --> 14:55.519
-How's the coffee
this morning, Lieutenant?
-I don't know, Cohen.

14:55.519 --> 14:57.354
Roberto Roca's
not the guy,

14:57.354 --> 15:00.065
and he's no help
with who else might've
been with Vasquez.

15:00.065 --> 15:03.485
-Well, Zorzi tested clean.
-Well, that's
one good thing.

15:03.485 --> 15:05.321
Desk downstairs
is sending a guy up.

15:05.321 --> 15:07.948
Says he saw something
last night on Essex Street.

15:07.948 --> 15:10.075
Anything else on
the cars that were
parked along there?

15:10.075 --> 15:13.621
No. Diane's
still working on that.

15:13.621 --> 15:17.249
-They told me the detectives
are upstairs.
-Yes, sir. Can I help you?

15:17.249 --> 15:19.877
I witnessed a shooting
last night when I was
driving my cab.

15:19.877 --> 15:22.254
Mm-hmm. Where was this at?
On Essex Street.

15:22.254 --> 15:25.549
I didn't report it
when it happened.
I apologize for that.

15:25.549 --> 15:27.635
I'm Detective Sipowicz.
This is Detective Simone.
What's your name?

15:27.635 --> 15:30.763
I'm Rajnish Prasad.

15:30.763 --> 15:32.431
Let's go talk down here.

15:32.431 --> 15:34.391
Thank you.

15:36.226 --> 15:38.187
I made a right turn
onto Essex Street.

15:38.187 --> 15:41.065
I saw an Italian man
running out of the market.

15:41.065 --> 15:42.942
He was pointing a gun
at two other men...

15:42.942 --> 15:45.945
who were standing by
a car across the street.

15:45.945 --> 15:49.698
The Italian shoots twice,
hits one of those other men--
a Puerto Rican.

15:49.698 --> 15:52.826
Wait a minute.
You're rolling by, right?
It's night.

15:52.826 --> 15:54.995
How do you take note
that one of these guys
is Italian,

15:54.995 --> 15:57.039
the other one's
Puerto Rican?
I know that store.

15:57.039 --> 16:00.292
The Koreans own that store.
They can barely
speak English.

16:00.292 --> 16:02.461
They barely even try.

16:02.461 --> 16:04.797
Anyway, when I
see this happening,
I wonder if the owner...

16:04.797 --> 16:07.091
had chased a thief
out into the street.

16:07.091 --> 16:09.176
But the man in the doorway
is white.

16:09.176 --> 16:11.261
Not Korean.
And how do you know
he's Italian?

16:11.261 --> 16:13.681
I've seen enough
of them to know.
Believe me.

16:13.681 --> 16:16.850
Get in the cab, they don't
have a polite word to say.
Give you 25 cents for a tip.

16:16.850 --> 16:20.646
Are you sure on
the number of men you saw
standing by the car?

16:20.646 --> 16:22.815
Two men.
My impression--

16:22.815 --> 16:25.484
The Puerto Rican was
robbing the other one.

16:25.484 --> 16:29.113
My first week driving a cab,
a Puerto Rican boy stuck
a gun to my head.

16:29.113 --> 16:32.616
Welcome to New York.
You see anyone fleeing
the scene, Mr. Prasad?

16:32.616 --> 16:34.493
No. Nobody was fleeing
the scene.

16:34.493 --> 16:37.329
Was my impression right?

16:37.329 --> 16:39.873
The Puerto Rican
was robbing the other one?
We're piecing that together.

16:39.873 --> 16:41.959
Because even so,
that's no excuse...

16:41.959 --> 16:44.712
for the Italian
to shoot him in the street
like John Wayne.

16:44.712 --> 16:46.422
Robbery should be
handled by the police.

16:46.422 --> 16:48.590
Without law,
we don't have a city.
We have a jungle.

16:48.590 --> 16:51.260
Thanks very much
for coming in.

16:51.260 --> 16:54.972
We may call you
in a few days.
You're welcome.

16:54.972 --> 16:57.641
SIPOWICZ:
Thank you.

16:57.641 --> 16:59.685
The other way.

16:59.685 --> 17:02.104
We gotta call
that asshole Baumgartner...

17:02.104 --> 17:04.606
and have him let us know
when Zorzi gets back.

17:04.606 --> 17:06.400
Ask him about what
this guy's saying.

17:06.400 --> 17:08.068
