And, uh, tested myself.
Made sure I'd cooled out.

33:05.942 --> 33:09.112
-Uh-huh.
-Uh--

33:10.571 --> 33:15.326
I don't know.
Must've been, like,
20 minutes or so...

33:15.326 --> 33:17.662
and I went back upstairs.

33:17.662 --> 33:20.373
Like a half hour.

33:20.373 --> 33:23.001
And--

33:23.001 --> 33:25.878
She was, uh,
lying on the floor--

33:25.878 --> 33:27.588
Michelle--

33:27.588 --> 33:28.923
with, uh,

33:30.550 --> 33:32.427
all these holes
in her chest.

33:32.427 --> 33:35.221
Somebody must have
broke in and stabbed her.

33:35.221 --> 33:38.433
What it must have been.
Will.

33:38.433 --> 33:42.437
You know that's not
what happened.

33:42.437 --> 33:43.855
No, it is.

33:43.855 --> 33:45.815
That's exactly
what must have happened.

33:47.275 --> 33:49.110
How'd her body
get in that Dumpster?

33:50.695 --> 33:53.239
Uh, well, with that, I--

33:53.239 --> 33:54.991
See, I just kind of--
I don't know--
I kind of freaked out.

33:54.991 --> 33:59.829
You know, when I saw her
I didn't know what to do,
and, uh--

33:59.829 --> 34:04.292
And so I took her
and I put her in there.

34:04.292 --> 34:05.835
I mean, I know that
that was wrong,

34:05.835 --> 34:08.212
and that was why
I was driving around
so upset afterwards.

34:08.212 --> 34:13.468
But I didn't kill her.
I mean, I swear
I didn't kill her.

34:13.468 --> 34:15.720
You felt something
for this girl?

34:15.720 --> 34:17.138
Yeah.

34:20.475 --> 34:25.063
Well, I'm looking at these
photographs here--
what was done to her.

34:27.315 --> 34:30.443
Do you want
to go into court,
they show these pictures,

34:30.443 --> 34:34.405
and it looks like
you just cold-bloodedly
killed her?

34:37.658 --> 34:40.661
I've heard
how it can be with coke.

34:40.661 --> 34:42.830
You do things.

34:42.830 --> 34:45.083
It's like
a blackout almost.

34:45.083 --> 34:47.335
And it's like
someone else did it.

34:47.335 --> 34:48.961
Was it like that?

34:50.129 --> 34:51.589
Yeah.

34:53.299 --> 34:54.967
It was.

34:56.636 --> 35:01.307
-What did you
stab her with, Will?
-A screwdriver.

35:03.309 --> 35:07.647
I'm telling you, man,
I don't remember doing it.

35:07.647 --> 35:12.819
Will, do you remember
and just feel awful?

35:12.819 --> 35:15.404
Like you'd do anything
if it hadn't happened?

35:18.116 --> 35:19.992
Yeah.

35:22.703 --> 35:25.039
You want to write it down
for me?

35:25.039 --> 35:28.376
Yeah, but I--
In a minute.

35:28.376 --> 35:29.836
Okay.

35:34.298 --> 35:37.343
My wife's been in and out
of private hospitals.

35:37.343 --> 35:39.554
Five different shrinks.

35:39.554 --> 35:43.558
The expense is incredible,
apart from just
the pressure of that...

35:43.558 --> 35:45.726
and trying to find
my own happiness.

35:45.726 --> 35:47.770
So I made this plan.

35:47.770 --> 35:50.189
Tony was like a courier,

35:50.189 --> 35:52.775
and him knowing
it was the mob's money,

35:52.775 --> 35:56.154
I knew there's no way
he's gonna give it up
to Joe Vasquez,

35:56.154 --> 36:00.533
which meant I knew
what I was gonna find
when I came out of that store.

36:00.533 --> 36:02.743
You'd predetermined you were
gonna kill Joe Vasquez--

36:02.743 --> 36:05.955
-And Tony?
-And when I was
inside the store,

36:05.955 --> 36:08.833
I put a glove on my left hand.

36:08.833 --> 36:10.960
So after I shot Vasquez,

36:10.960 --> 36:14.547
I ran up, got his gun,
and I shot Tony twice
with that.

36:14.547 --> 36:16.174
Also part of the plan?

36:16.174 --> 36:20.595
You see, this plan
just took hold in my mind.

36:20.595 --> 36:24.599
It was like an obsession.
I spent months planning this.

36:24.599 --> 36:27.185
How you were gonna
murder your friend,
and lie to the people...

36:27.185 --> 36:29.395
-that you work with.
-Detective.

36:29.395 --> 36:33.357
Tony used to torment me
with that money he was moving.

36:33.357 --> 36:36.152
We'd be in the car--
"Hey, Mike.

36:36.152 --> 36:39.155
"You ever seen
a million dollars?

36:39.155 --> 36:41.157
Go ahead, feel it."

36:41.157 --> 36:43.784
But still, see,
that's where it fell apart,

36:43.784 --> 36:47.371
because after
I had executed my plan--

36:47.371 --> 36:51.584
and gotten away with it--
the thing that really
bothered me...

36:51.584 --> 36:55.129
-was what I'd done
to my friend.
-Your friend Tony.

36:55.129 --> 36:56.422
Ayayay.

36:56.422 --> 36:58.216
Detective Sipowicz,
I'm gonna ask you
to refrain...

36:58.216 --> 37:01.385
-from this part
of the questioning.
-Yeah, sure.

37:01.385 --> 37:05.723
So, Tony's dead,
you shot Vasquez.
Now what?

37:05.723 --> 37:08.643
I put the attaché case
in the trunk
of my girlfriend's car.

37:08.643 --> 37:12.939
I tell you, if I'd have just
left the country
with that million dollars,

37:12.939 --> 37:15.191
I'd be long gone,

37:15.191 --> 37:16.692
and you guys
would be sitting here...

37:16.692 --> 37:18.611
scratching your balls.

37:18.611 --> 37:22.657
But smart like you are,
you figure you'll get away
with no one suspecting,

37:22.657 --> 37:24.283
right, Zorzi?

37:25.868 --> 37:29.038
That's why I came up
with the second robber
getting away with the money.

37:29.038 --> 37:31.624
-Yeah, your phantom
Puerto Rican number two.
-Detective!

37:31.624 --> 37:36.754
You're right.
Let me get the hell out of here,
breathe some clean air.

37:36.754 --> 37:38.839
-You hear this moron?
-Shh.

37:38.839 --> 37:41.676
What I didn't figure
was you finding out
about Trish.

37:41.676 --> 37:44.053
Oh, yeah, that was a tough one.

37:44.053 --> 37:45.263
He didn't figure
that we would canvass
the plates...

37:45.263 --> 37:47.890
-at the crime scene.
-Sipowicz.

37:47.890 --> 37:50.559
That caught me by surprise.

37:50.559 --> 37:52.812
I should have never let her
be part of this.

37:52.812 --> 37:55.064
Didn't figure
we'd come up with Trish,

37:55.064 --> 37:57.775
didn't think we'd tear down
this phantom Puerto Rican
number two--

37:57.775 --> 38:01.279
which took us about 27 minutes,
you murdering scumbag nitwit!

38:01.279 --> 38:03.447
Will someone shut him up?

38:03.447 --> 38:06.158
I'm all right.
I'm all right.

38:07.910 --> 38:10.830
I'm all right.
I'm all right.

38:26.929 --> 38:30.725
-Zorzi's going?
-He's in there with I.A.B.

38:30.725 --> 38:33.394
-No remorse at all.
-All my heart
I thought you guys...

38:33.394 --> 38:36.272
were on the wrong track.

38:36.272 --> 38:39.400
Probably I.A.B.'s gonna want
to make it look like
they cracked the case, huh?

38:39.400 --> 38:41.694
So now it's you and us,
right, Baumgartner?

38:41.694 --> 38:44.488
Stand-up cops
against the Rat Squad?

38:44.488 --> 38:48.492
You notice any stripes
on my arms, Sipowicz?

38:48.492 --> 38:51.871
You never gave a damn
about Zorzi.

38:52.496 --> 38:54.040
You're a mean drunk--

38:54.040 --> 38:58.502
Decides the shift agitating
over Zorzi is how you're
gonna make people miserable.

38:58.502 --> 39:01.630
And you can shove
those stripes up your ass.

39:01.630 --> 39:04.884
Nothing worse
than a reformed souse.

39:04.884 --> 39:07.178
Before you get
all disciplinary, Sarge,

39:07.178 --> 39:09.555
you just remember
that you invited
Detective Sipowicz here...

39:09.555 --> 39:12.892
to cup his hands for you,
and I was the witness.

39:21.025 --> 39:23.944
Now my insides in an upheaval,
the nighttime too,

39:23.944 --> 39:26.238
not hitting this imbecile.

39:31.786 --> 39:34.705
Hey. I been beeping Russell
the last couple hours.

39:34.705 --> 39:36.415
I'm worried over her.

39:41.962 --> 39:44.256
Hey, uh,

39:44.256 --> 39:46.008
I gotta take
a rain check.

39:46.008 --> 39:48.552
-Sure.
-Sorry.

39:50.137 --> 39:51.847
I understand.

39:57.728 --> 40:00.981
-I'm gonna look where
her and me had coffee.
-Yeah.

40:00.981 --> 40:02.983
Let me go to that Patrick's.

40:02.983 --> 40:05.361
-Where she was at
with Liery?
-Mm-hmm.

40:05.361 --> 40:11.242
Yeah, that could be.

40:11.242 --> 40:14.245
♪♪

40:37.726 --> 40:42.022
Diane.

40:42.022 --> 40:44.233
Me and Andy--
We been looking
all over for you.

40:44.233 --> 40:47.820
-I'm sorry.
-Don't be sorry.
You're all right.

40:47.820 --> 40:50.573
-Something's wrong.
-Okay.

40:50.573 --> 40:54.410
-I'm okay.
I haven't been drinking.
-That's good.

40:54.410 --> 40:56.245
Something's wrong.
(whimpering)

40:56.245 --> 40:57.455
Come on.

41:03.085 --> 41:06.630
I'm gonna put
some water on right now.
I'm gonna make some tea, okay?

41:06.630 --> 41:07.673
I just want to sit down
for a minute.

41:07.673 --> 41:10.676
You go ahead. Do that.

41:10.676 --> 41:14.180
Diane.

41:14.180 --> 41:15.556
What do you think's wrong?

41:15.556 --> 41:17.683
'Cause it's frightening.

41:17.683 --> 41:20.478
-I don't know.
-I don't want a drink,
but I feel...

41:20.478 --> 41:24.064
like I'm almost dizzy,
and afraid, like things
don't exactly look real--

41:24.064 --> 41:26.859
Like, I'll look at you
and I know you're
next to me,

41:26.859 --> 41:29.278
but then it
looks like you're
15 feet away or so.

41:29.278 --> 41:31.780
Diane, I need you to try
to take it easy for me
a little bit.

41:31.780 --> 41:35.284
-Okay?
-I left because it was
happening in the squad,

41:35.284 --> 41:38.662
but then it was happening
while I was walking around.

41:38.662 --> 41:40.456
I'm glad you came over here,

41:40.456 --> 41:43.292
-but I want you to try
and take it easy, all right?
-I'm scaring you.

41:43.292 --> 41:47.296
No. Not at all.

41:47.296 --> 41:49.924
I don't want to be
like this forever.
I can't stand it.

41:49.924 --> 41:52.468
Hey. Come here, come here,
come here, come here.

41:53.385 --> 41:55.930
(sobs)

41:55.930 --> 42:00.351
What is it?
Hmm? Can you think
of what it is?

42:00.351 --> 42:02.728
Can you tell me what it is
that's scaring you?

42:02.728 --> 42:06.232
I-I--
I think something happened.

42:06.232 --> 42:08.692
With Liery--
When he drugged you that time.

42:08.692 --> 42:10.569
Hmm?

42:12.071 --> 42:14.698
Something happened, Bobby.

42:15.908 --> 42:18.536
Yeah, we're gonna
get through it.

42:18.536 --> 42:20.037
Okay?

42:21.539 --> 42:24.416
Don't you doubt
that I love you.

42:26.502 --> 42:28.671
I'm sorry for what I did.

42:28.671 --> 42:30.047
I-I didn't mean that
to happen.

42:30.047 --> 42:32.883
No, Diane, it was the job
that put you through that.

42:32.883 --> 42:34.969
You didn't ask
for what happened there.

42:34.969 --> 42:38.514
If I led him on.
If I was a flirt.

42:38.514 --> 42:40.474
No, no.

42:43.185 --> 42:46.397
I just didn't
want him to yell,
so I must have flirted.

42:51.026 --> 42:52.945
This guy--
He broke bad with you, right?

42:52.945 --> 42:55.322
He broke bad with you--
Liery?

42:58.242 --> 43:00.369
I didn't know--

43:00.369 --> 43:03.205
I didn't know
that would happen.

43:04.498 --> 43:07.167
I was only 12.

43:09.253 --> 43:12.381
I didn't know
that would happen,

43:12.381 --> 43:15.551
and I don't
even think I flirted.

43:19.555 --> 43:21.640
-Oh, Diane.
-I just--

43:23.100 --> 43:25.978
I, uh--
(sniffles)

43:25.978 --> 43:28.147
just woke up
and he was finished.

43:37.531 --> 43:39.199
I--I just--

43:39.199 --> 43:42.077
I didn't want him
to yell at me
like Mom and Dougie.

43:42.077 --> 43:44.330
It's okay.

43:44.330 --> 43:47.291
I must have flirted,
but I don't think I did.

43:49.335 --> 43:51.587
Okay.

43:51.587 --> 43:54.590
It's out now.
You know, you got it out.

43:55.591 --> 43:57.593
I had to keep a secret.

43:57.593 --> 44:00.179
-Daddy's pretty pet.
-You got it out.

44:03.557 --> 44:06.101
I don't want
to be this way.

44:06.101 --> 44:08.812
I can't stand if I'm gonna
be like this.

44:11.523 --> 44:13.359
(sobbing)

44:15.194 --> 44:17.279
I'm gonna hold you.
I'm gonna hold you.

44:17.279 --> 44:19.031
I want to hold tight
to you.

44:19.031 --> 44:21.241
Hold tight.

44:21.241 --> 44:23.118
I'm right here.

44:26.372 --> 44:29.917
You're gonna be all right.
We're gonna be all right.

44:34.254 --> 44:36.256
You're gonna be all right.

44:45.724 --> 44:48.727
♪♪
